{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"For outpatient services, most quarters showed relative stability, interrupted by three notable shifts.

Outpatient visits and OPD curative visits moved in parallel, increasing in Q3 2024 (+10.8% and +11.4%, respectively), followed by sharp declines in Q1 2025 (-15.2% and -14.9%), and then a strong rebound in Q3 2025 (+16.0% and +15.2%).

OPD curative follow-up visits declined earlier and more steeply, falling in Q4 2024 (-19.7%) and again in Q1 2025 (-11.3%), before increasing in Q3 2025 (+18.8%).","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"ce37ee8a-6591-4557-9937-48b73b070bc9","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Quarter-to-quarter change in service volume, outpatient visits","useFooter":false,"footerText":""}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"Trends for outpatient visits including outpatient curative visits followed expected volumes through 2023, experiencing surpluses and subsequent periods of disruption in the second half of 2024 before reaching expected values again for 2025, with a brief period of surplus in OPD curative care averaging 7.6% higher than expected values rom July-September 2025. 

OPD curative follow-up visits experienced periods of disruption through 2023 and 2024, and 2025 (averaging -7.2%) followed by a period of surplus at the end of 2025 from May 2025-September 2025 averaging +21%. 


","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"0afcdcb1-a701-44eb-9f17-94c69f01ebce","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Outpatient visit trends in 2025 largely aligned with expected levels","useFooter":false,"footerText":""}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"Measles first-dose vaccination declined substantially through 2024–25, falling by roughly 35–40% from its December 2024 peak to a low in mid-2025, before showing a modest rebound in recent months.

Second-dose coverage remained consistently lower and more volatile, with brief spikes during peak periods but persistent drops during mid-year months, indicating weak follow-through.

A large completion gap persists, with second doses averaging only 25–35% of first doses, raising concerns about incomplete immunization and herd immunity risks."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"891479dd-025e-4c32-b6bb-3da497bba932","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in measles vaccination"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"IPV 1st dose coverage has declined steadily since late 2023, falling by roughly 12–15% from ~10,500 doses to ~9,000 by mid-2025.

