{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"Institutional deliveries rose gradually through 2024 before climbing more sharply in 2025, reaching nearly 24,000 by mid-2025, reflecting stronger uptake of facility births.

Postnatal care for newborns increased steadily, reaching about 21,000 by mid-2025, indicating improvements in early follow-up after delivery.

Postnatal care for mothers followed a similar upward trend, with notable gains in 2025 to nearly 24,000 visits, pointing to stronger continuity of care across the maternal–newborn period.","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"b8b90459-b480-4f99-9a96-205a44d72207","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in deliveries and postnatal care services","useFooter":false,"footerText":""}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"In 2025, deliveries rose steadily above expected levels, reaching ~14% higher than trend by June. This shows stronger uptake of facility-based births — a key entry point for maternal–newborn care.

Newborn PNC visits rose to ~8% above expected by June 2025, but gains are smaller than for deliveries. While gains are smaller than for deliveries, volumes still reached about 90% of delivery levels, suggesting some newborns are not receiving timely follow-up after birth.

Maternal PNC visits climbed to ~9% above expected by June 2025. PNC for mothers reached about 93% of delivery levels, pointing to modest but persistent gaps in linking facility births with postpartum care."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"42d3fcf1-a5a9-4078-9ffa-d9522b99a42b","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Institutional deliveries and PNC visits rise above expected levels in 2025, but continuity of care gap remains"}}

