{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"Surpluses in BCG, Penta1, and Penta3 vaccination broadly followed each other, following expected trends with periods of surplus. 

The periods of greatest surplus for BCG, Penta1, and Penta3 occurred in September 2024 (+24.4% for BCG) (+23.1% for Penta1) and (+19.1% for Penta2). 

In 2025, Penta1 and Penta3 vaccination followed expected trends, while BCG vaccination had 2 brief periods of surplus, averaging 7% above expected from March-July 2025. "},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"2562c43a-1b26-48a3-a872-b9740f37af04","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"All vaccines had surplus in 2024; BCG Remains in Surplus in 2025 as Penta1 and Penta3 Follow Trend"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"Trends for outpatient visits including outpatient curative visits followed expected volumes through 2023, experiencing surpluses and subsequent periods of disruption in the second half of 2024 before reaching expected values again for 2025, with a brief period of surplus in OPD curative care averaging 7.6% higher than expected values rom July-September 2025. 

OPD curative follow-up visits experienced periods of disruption through 2023 and 2024, and 2025 (averaging -7.2%) followed by a period of surplus at the end of 2025 from May 2025-September 2025 averaging +21%. 


